<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Greetings all! Geiger: My suggestions.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:50 p.m. 15/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Greetings all! Geiger: My suggestions.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>PVP looks alive and well on the PVP server and I have been having quite the blast playin it these last days. I have found a few things that I thought could be improved upon as follows:

<P>1. Would it be possible to EXCLUDE specific individuals from receiving one's SHOUTS or OOC regardless of their language ability? The reason I ask is that I know of SOME guilds that are notorious for inserting spys IE creating a 1st level Dark Elf JUST so that person can listen to the Dark Elves and see what they are up too. Sometimes it is obvious who this person is and it would by nice of we could not only permnantly IGNORE such a person...but make it so HE permnantly ignores you too.
<P>2. Factions: What happened to them in PVP? If a Dark Elf kills a fellow Dark Elf it is my belief that his faction standing should be altered accordingly. Otherwise we will end up having chaos reign beyond realism. Role play in the game dictates that the races at sorta stick together and this would aid in that endeavor.
<P>Hmmm well I can't recall the 3rd. In any case, I have enjoyed the PVP server greatly and look forward to joining it in the retail as well!
<P>Gray Rage
<BR>DarkenBAne Company
<P>PS CC sucks :P
<BR>PSS Same with the Teverils *grins*
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
